        "\n",
        "### Q2: Bug Diagnosis (8 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Two buggy functions need fixing. Read the buggy code, understand the problem, then write a corrected version.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "**Bug A (4 pts):** This function tries to extract the Gini coefficient from REST Countries API data. But it crashes because `gini` is a nested dict like `{\"2019\": 35.1}`, not a float:\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "# BUGGY:\n",
        "def flatten_gini(countries_list):\n",
        "    result = []\n",
        "    for c in countries_list:\n",
        "        result.append({\n",
        "            'name': c['name'],\n",
        "            'gini': c.get('gini', 0)  # BUG: gini is a dict, not a number!\n",
        "        })\n",
        "    return pd.DataFrame(result)\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "Write `fix_flatten_gini(countries_list)` that correctly extracts the *most recent* Gini value from the nested dict. If `gini` is missing or empty, use `None`.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "**Bug B (4 pts):** This merge function doesn't check for empty-string keys, causing a cartesian explosion:\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "# BUGGY:\n",
        "def merge_data(left, right, key):\n",
        "    return pd.merge(left, right, on=key)  # BUG: empty keys cause explosion!\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "Write `fix_safe_merge(left, right, key)` that drops rows with empty-string or NaN values in the key column before merging."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "b-wfbONnepBy"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def fix_flatten_gini(countries_list):\n",
        "    result = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for c in countries_list:\n",
        "        gini_data = c.get('gini')\n",
        "\n",
        "        if isinstance(gini_data, dict) and len(gini_data) > 0:\n",
        "            latest_year = max(gini_data.keys(), key=lambda x: int(x))\n",
        "            gini_value = gini_data[latest_year]\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            gini_value = None\n",
        "\n",
        "        result.append({\n",
        "            'name': c.get('name'),\n",
        "            'gini_value': gini_value\n",
        "        })\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pd.DataFrame(result)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def fix_safe_merge(left, right, key):\n",
        "    left_clean = left[left[key].notna() & (left[key] != \"\")]\n",
        "    right_clean = right[right[key].notna() & (right[key] != \"\")]\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pd.merge(left_clean, right_clean, on=key, how='inner')"
      ]
    },
