        "### Q3: Code Evaluation (7 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Two approaches to fetching 5 years of daily exchange rates from the Frankfurter API:\n",
        "\n",
        "**Implementation A** (loop per date):\n",
        "```python\n",
        "import urllib.request, json\n",
        "\n",
        "def fetch_rates_loop(start, end):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Fetch one day at a time.\"\"\"\n",
        "    from datetime import date, timedelta\n",
        "    results = {}\n",
        "    current = date.fromisoformat(start)\n",
        "    end_date = date.fromisoformat(end)\n",
        "    while current <= end_date:\n",
        "        url = f'https://api.frankfurter.app/{current}?from=USD&to=INR'\n",
        "        resp = urllib.request.urlopen(url)\n",
        "        data = json.loads(resp.read())\n",
        "        results[str(current)] = data['rates']['INR']\n",
        "        current += timedelta(days=1)\n",
        "    return results\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Implementation B** (single range query):\n",
        "```python\n",
        "def fetch_rates_range(start, end):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Fetch entire range in one call.\"\"\"\n",
        "    url = f'https://api.frankfurter.app/{start}..{end}?from=USD&to=INR'\n",
        "    resp = urllib.request.urlopen(url)\n",
        "    data = json.loads(resp.read())\n",
        "    return data['rates']\n",
