        "\n",
        "### Q5: Currency Trend Analysis (15 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Write a function that takes daily exchange rate data and computes monthly trends for a given currency.\n",
        "\n",
        "The function should:\n",
        "1. Extract the `date` and chosen currency columns\n",
        "2. Set `date` as a DatetimeIndex\n",
        "3. Resample to **month-end** frequency using the mean rate\n",
        "4. Compute a **rolling mean** over the given window (on the monthly data)\n",
        "5. Compute **month-over-month percent change**\n",
        "6. Add a **depreciating** boolean column: `True` when the monthly rate > rolling mean (currency weakened vs USD)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "s6f-JJcCepB3"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def analyze_currency_trends(fx_df, currency, window=3):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Analyze currency trends from daily exchange rate data.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Args:\n",
        "        fx_df: DataFrame with 'date' column and currency columns (e.g., 'INR', 'EUR')\n",
        "        currency: Currency code string (e.g., 'INR')\n",
        "        window: Rolling window size for monthly data (default 3)\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns:\n",
        "        DataFrame with columns:\n",
        "            - date (DatetimeIndex, month-end)\n",
        "            - rate (the raw currency column values, resampled)\n",
        "            - monthly_avg (monthly mean of daily rates)\n",
        "            - rolling_mean (rolling window mean on monthly_avg)\n",
        "            - pct_change (month-over-month percent change of monthly_avg)\n",
        "            - depreciating (bool: monthly_avg > rolling_mean)\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    # YOUR CODE HERE\n",
        "    df = fx_df.copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    df = df[['date', currency]]\n",
        "\n",
        "    df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'])\n",
        "    df = df.set_index('date')\n",
        "\n",
        "    monthly = df.resample('M').mean()\n",
        "    monthly = monthly.rename(columns={currency: 'monthly_avg'})\n",
        "\n",
        "    monthly['rolling_mean'] = monthly['monthly_avg'].rolling(window=window).mean()\n",
        "    monthly['pct_change'] = monthly['monthly_avg'].pct_change()\n",
        "    monthly['depreciating'] = monthly['monthly_avg'] > monthly['rolling_mean']\n",
        "\n",
        "    monthly['rate'] = monthly['monthly_avg']\n",
        "\n",
        "    # FIX: bring date back as column\n",
        "    monthly = monthly.reset_index()\n",
        "\n",
        "    return monthly[['date', 'rate', 'monthly_avg', 'rolling_mean', 'pct_change', 'depreciating']]"
      ]
    },
